  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, there are several great smartphones available in India under \u20b912,000. Here are a few notable options that were popular and highly regarded:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50**:\n   - Display: 6.6 inches, FHD+\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - RAM: Up to 6 GB\n   - Storage: Up to 128 GB, expandable via microSD\n   - Battery: 5000 mAh with fast charging\n   - Camera: 50 MP (primary) + 2 MP (macro) + 2 MP (depth), 16 MP front\n\n2. **Redmi Note 11**:\n   - Display: 6.43 inches, FHD+\n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 680\n   - RAM: Up to 6 GB\n   - Storage: Up to 128 GB, expandable via microSD\n   - Battery: 5000 mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - Camera: 50 MP (main) + 8 MP (ultrawide) + 2 MP (macro) + 2 MP (depth), 13 MP front\n\n3. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - Display: 6.43 inches, FHD+\n   - Processor: MediaTek Dimensity 810\n   - RAM: Up to 6 GB\n   - Storage: Up to 128 GB, expandable via microSD\n   - Battery: 5000 mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - Camera: 64 MP (main) + 8 MP (ultrawide) + 2 MP (macro), 16 MP front\n\n4. **Samsung Galaxy M13**:\n   - Display: 6.6 inches, FHD+\n   - Processor: Exynos 850\n   - RAM: Up to 6 GB\n   - Storage: Up to 128 GB, expandable via microSD\n   - Battery: 6000 mAh\n   - Camera: 50 MP (main) + 5 MP (ultrawide) + 2 MP (macro), 8 MP front\n\n5. **Infinix Note 12**:\n   - Display: 6.7 inches, FHD+\n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G88\n   - RAM: Up to 8 GB\n   - Storage: Up to 128 GB, expandable via microSD\n   - Battery: 5000 mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - Camera: 50 MP (main) + 2 MP (depth), 16 MP front\n\nWhen choosing the best smartphone for your needs, consider factors such as camera quality, battery life, performance, and user interface. Prices may vary by retailer and location, so it's a good idea to check for discounts or deals before making a purchase.",
